  <xs:simpleType name="StatsValuesEnumType">
    <xs:annotation>
      <xs:documentation>
        The StatsValuesEnumType enumerates the various statistical values
        that may be accumulated. This documentation shows the expansion
        of abbreviations and the name of a related element in
        Statistics.xsd. See explanations of the elements in Statistics.xsd.
         ACL = acceptance control limit
         AOQ = average outgoing quality
         AOQL = average outgoing quality limit
         AV = appraiser variation (AppraiserVariation)
         AVG = average (Average)
         AVGRNG = average range (AverageRange)
         BIAS = bias (Bias)
         CM = 8-sigma manufacturing capability index (Cm)
         CMK = 8-sigma manufacturing capability index (Cmk)
         CP = capability index over all subgroups (Cp)
         CPK = capability indexover all subgroups (Cpk)
         CPKL = process capability index, lower (CpkL)
         CPKU = process capability index, upper (CpkU)
         CPM = capability index with respect to target specification (Cpm)
         DIFF = difference (Difference)
         EFFNUM = effective number (EffectiveNumber)
         ESTSTDV = estimated standard deviation
                   (EstimatedStandardDeviation)
         EV = equipment variation (EquipmentVariation)
         INTCPT = intercept (RegressionIntercept)
         INTERACTION = interaction (Interaction)
         KURT = kurtosis (Kurtosis)
         LCL = lower control limit (LowerControlLimit)
         LCLRNG = lower control limit range (LowerControlLimitRange)
         LNRTY = linearity (Linearity)
         LQL = limiting quality level
         LWRCONFLIM = lower confidence limit (LowerConfidenceLimit)
         MAX = maximum (Maximum)
         MIN = minimum (Minimum)
         NOOTHI = number out of tolerance high (NumberOverUpperTolerance)
         NOOTLO = number out of tolerance low (NumberUnderLowerTolerance)
         NORM = normality (Normality)
         NUMOOC = number out of control (NumberOutOfControl)
         NUMOOT = number out of tolerance (NumberOutOfTolerance)
         NUMSUB = number subgroups (NumberSubgroups)
         PM = machine performance index (Pm)
         PMK = machine performance index, minimum (Pmk)
         PMKL = machine performance index, lower (PmkL)
         PMKU = machine performance index, upper (PmkU)
         PP = processperformance index (Pp)
         PPK = process performance index, minimum (Ppk)
         PPKL = process performance index, lower (PpkL)
         PPKU = process performance index, upper (PpkU)
         PROVAR = process variation (ProcessVariation)
         PV = part variation (PartVariation)
         QK = process variation index
         RANDR = repeatability and reproducibility (GageRandR)
         RANGE = range (Range)
         REL_AV = relative appraiser variation (RelativeAppraiserVariation)
         REL_BIAS = relative bias (RelativeBias)
         REL_EV = relative equipment variation (RelativeEquipmentVariation)
         REL_INTERACTION = relative interaction (RelativeInteraction)
         REL_LNRTY = relative linearity (RelativeLinearity)
         REL_PV = relative part variation (RelativePartVariation)
         REL_RANDR = rel repeatability and reproducibility
                     (RelativeGageRandR)
         REL_TV = relative total variation (RelativeTotalVariation)
         RMS = root mean square (RootMeanSquare)
         R_SQR = R squared (GoodnessOfFit)
         SKEW = skew (Skew)
         SLOPE = slope (RegressionSlope)
         STDDEV = standard deviation (StandardDeviation)
         TDIST = T distribution (TDistribution)
         TOTNUM = total number (TotalNumber)
         TV = total variaton (TotalVariation)
         UCL = upper control limit (UpperControlLimit)
         UCLRNG = upper control limit range (UpperControlLimitRange)
         UDL = user defined limit
         UPRCONFLIM = upper confidence limit (UpperConfidenceLimit)
        The following from the full list are found in ISO 3534-2
         ACL
         AOQ
         AOQL
         CP
         CPK
         CPKL
         CPKU
         LCL
         LQL
         PP
         PPK
         PPKL
         PPKU
         QK
         UCL
        The following from the full list are found in ISO 22514-3
         PM
         PMK
         PMKL
         PMKU
      </xs:documentation>
    </xs:annotation>
    <xs:restriction base="xs:NMTOKEN">
      <xs:enumeration value="ACL"/>
      <xs:enumeration value="AOQ"/>
      <xs:enumeration value="AOQL"/>
      <xs:enumeration value="AV"/>
      <xs:enumeration value="AVG"/>
      <xs:enumeration value="AVGRNG"/>
      <xs:enumeration value="BIAS"/>
      <xs:enumeration value="CM"/>
      <xs:enumeration value="CMK"/>
